# Talk to Data — Frontend Implementation Plan

> **Source:** [Frontend_Master.md](file:///Users/vanshgupta/gina/Gina_cfp/docs/Frontend_Master.md)  
> **Stack:** Next.js 14 (App Router) · Tailwind CSS · Recharts · `@supabase/ssr` · TypeScript  
> **Backend:** Fastify on port 3001 — routes for datasets, conversations, messages already implemented

---

## Phase 1 — Project Scaffold & Foundation

> **Goal:** Get a building Next.js app with types, env config, and API client ready. Nothing visual yet.

### Task 1.1 — Initialize Next.js project
Create the Next.js 14 app inside `frontend/` using `create-next-app` with TypeScript, Tailwind, App Router, and `src-dir=false`.

```bash
npx -y create-next-app@14 frontend --typescript --tailwind --app --src-dir=false
```

**Output:** `frontend/` directory with working `npm run dev`.

---

### Task 1.2 — Install dependencies
Install all required packages per §10 of Frontend_Master.md.

```bash
npm install @supabase/supabase-js @supabase/ssr recharts papaparse clsx tailwind-merge
npm install -D @types/papaparse
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Use `@supabase/ssr` — NOT the deprecated `@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs`.

---

### Task 1.3 — Create `.env.local` template
Create `.env.local` with the three required variables:

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxx.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=xxx
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001
```

---

### Task 1.4 — Create folder structure (empty directories)
Create all directories from §1 — no component files yet, just folders so future imports resolve:

```
components/landing/
components/sidebar/
components/upload/
components/chat/
components/output/
components/charts/
components/pinned/
components/semantic/
components/shared/
lib/supabase/
lib/api/
lib/pii/
lib/hooks/
types/
app/auth/callback/
app/app/
```

---

### Task 1.5 — Create `types/index.ts`
Copy all TypeScript interfaces from §7 of Frontend_Master.md:
- `Dataset`, `SemanticState`, `ColumnProfile`
- `Conversation`, `Message`, `OutputPayload`
- `ChartData`, `BigNumberData`
- `PipelineStep`, `QueryPayload`

---

### Task 1.6 — Create API client (`lib/api/client.ts`)
Typed fetch wrapper that:
1. Gets the Supabase session (browser-side, `getSession()` is safe here)
2. Attaches `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` to every request
3. Throws on non-2xx responses with parsed error message

This is used for all **non-SSE** requests.

---

### Task 1.7 — Create API module: datasets (`lib/api/datasets.ts`)
Thin wrappers calling `apiFetch`:
- `listDatasets()` → `GET /api/datasets`
- `uploadDataset(file: File)` → `POST /api/datasets/upload` (multipart/form-data — no JSON Content-Type)
- `getSemanticState(datasetId)` → `GET /api/datasets/:id/semantic`
- `patchSemanticState(datasetId, corrections)` → `PATCH /api/datasets/:id/semantic`

---

### Task 1.8 — Create API module: conversations (`lib/api/conversations.ts`)
- `listConversations(datasetId)` → `GET /api/datasets/:id/conversations`
- `createConversation(datasetId, title?)` → `POST /api/datasets/:id/conversations`

---

### Task 1.9 — Create API module: messages (`lib/api/messages.ts`)
- `getMessages(conversationId)` → `GET /api/conversations/:id/messages`

Maps snake_case from backend to camelCase types.

---

## Phase 2 — Authentication Layer

> **Goal:** Google OAuth login → JWT → protected `/app` routes. No UI beyond auth modal.

### Task 2.1 — Supabase browser client (`lib/supabase/client.ts`)
Create using `createBrowserClient` from `@supabase/ssr`:

```typescript
import { createBrowserClient } from '@supabase/ssr';

export const supabase = createBrowserClient(
  process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
  process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!
);
```

---

### Task 2.2 — Supabase server client (`lib/supabase/server.ts`)
Create using `createServerClient` from `@supabase/ssr` — used in middleware and the auth callback route handler.

---

### Task 2.3 — OAuth callback handler (`app/auth/callback/route.ts`)
- Reads `code` from query params
- Exchanges code for session using Supabase server client
- Redirects to `/app`

---

### Task 2.4 — Auth middleware (`middleware.ts`)
- Uses `createServerClient` from `@supabase/ssr`
- Calls `supabase.auth.getUser()` (NOT `getSession()` — security requirement)
- Blocks all `/app/*` routes if no valid user
- Redirects to `/` (landing page)
- Matcher: `/app/:path*`

> [!WARNING]
> Must use `getUser()` in server code — `getSession()` reads cookies without JWT validation and can be spoofed.

---

### Task 2.5 — `useAuth` hook (`lib/hooks/useAuth.ts`)
Provides: `user`, `session`, `signOut()`, `isLoading`
- Uses `supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange` listener
- Fires `POST /api/users/sync` on first session (fire-and-forget)

---

### Task 2.6 — Root layout with auth provider (`app/layout.tsx`)
- Load fonts (Inter from Google Fonts)
- Global Tailwind setup
- Wrap children in auth context provider
- HTML lang, meta viewport, title tag

---

### Task 2.7 — Landing page (`app/page.tsx`) + AuthModal
Minimal landing — just enough to test auth flow:
- "Talk to Data" wordmark
- Tagline + sub-copy
- "Get started" CTA → opens `AuthModal`
- `AuthModal` wraps Supabase `Auth` component with Google OAuth

> [!NOTE]
> Landing page gets polished later in Phase 7. This is a functional stub.

