## Phase 6 — Output Card & Charts

> **Goal:** Rich, styled output cards with narrative, charts, citations, confidence, and follow-ups.

### Task 6.1 — `OutputCard.tsx` — main output container
The complete result display after `result` SSE event. Assembles all sub-components:
- `KeyFigure` → `NarrativeText` → `ChartPanel` (collapsed) → `CitationChips` → `SQLExpand` → `ConfidenceIndicator` → `FollowUpSuggestions` → `SomethingOff`

---

### Task 6.2 — `KeyFigure.tsx`
Large prominent headline number/text. Renders `keyFigure` string as-is in large font.

---

### Task 6.3 — `NarrativeText.tsx`
2–3 sentence plain English explanation. Renders `narrative` string. No markdown parsing needed.

---

### Task 6.4 — `CitationChips.tsx`
Row of small pills: "based on: amount · category · quarter"
- Maps `citationChips: string[]` to styled pills

---

### Task 6.5 — `SQLExpand.tsx`
Accordion: "See how this was calculated"
- Collapsed by default
- Expands to show `sql` (and `secondarySql` if present) in `<pre>` monospace block

---

### Task 6.6 — `ConfidenceIndicator.tsx`
Progress bar with percentage:
- Green: score > 70
- Amber: score > 40
- Red: score ≤ 40
- Label: "Confidence: 82%"

---

### Task 6.7 — `FollowUpSuggestions.tsx`
2–3 clickable pill buttons:
- Maps `followUpSuggestions: string[]`
- On click: populate chat input text (do NOT auto-submit)

---

### Task 6.8 — `SomethingOff.tsx`
"Something off? ↗" link at bottom of output card. Click triggers `CorrectionModal` (wired in Phase 7).

---

### Task 6.9 — `ChartPanel.tsx` — chart dispatcher
- "See chart ▼" toggle — chart is **collapsed by default**
- When expanded, dispatches to correct chart component based on `chartType`
- Pin button appears only when chart is expanded

```typescript
switch (chartType) {
  case 'big_number': return <BigNumberCard />;
  case 'bar':        return <BarChart />;
  case 'line':       return <LineChart />;
  case 'grouped_bar': return <GroupedBarChart />;
  case 'stacked_bar': return <StackedBarChart />;
  case 'table':      return <DataTable />;
}
```

---

### Task 6.10 — `BigNumberCard.tsx`
Pure CSS — no Recharts. Large number + label text. Uses `keyFigure` string.

---

### Task 6.11 — `BarChart.tsx`
Recharts horizontal bar chart (`layout="vertical"`):
- Category on Y-axis, value on X-axis
- `chartData.labels` as categories, `chartData.datasets` as series
- NatWest palette: deep teal `#006D6F`, navy `#1D2B53`, amber `#F5A623`
- Tooltips on hover, no axis labels by default

---

### Task 6.12 — `LineChart.tsx`
Recharts line chart:
- X-axis = period labels from `labels[]`
- Same colour palette
- Tooltips on hover

---

### Task 6.13 — `GroupedBarChart.tsx`
Recharts grouped bar:
- Multiple datasets rendered as adjacent bars
- Side-by-side comparison

---

### Task 6.14 — `StackedBarChart.tsx`
Recharts stacked bar:
- `stackId="a"` on all `<Bar>` components
- Percentage labels on segments

---

### Task 6.15 — `DataTable.tsx`
Tailwind-styled table fallback:
- Max 10 rows shown initially
- "Show more" expand button for remaining rows

---

### Task 6.16 — `PinButton.tsx`
Pin icon button:
- Only visible when chart is expanded
- On click: emits pin event up to `ChatView`
- Icon changes to filled when pinned

---

### Task 6.17 — `PinnedOutputPanel.tsx`
Right-side panel:
- Hidden by default (0 width)
- Slides in with CSS transition (200ms) when chart is pinned
- Shows: pinned chart + key figure
- "Unpin ✕" button at top right
- Only one pinned chart at a time — new pin replaces old

